<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Applied_state_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Applied_state_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Applied_state_assignment">
Applied state assignment allows a subject to have <b>State</b> or to be in a <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Applied_state_assignment  Attribute: assigned_to 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Applied_state_assignment.assigned_to"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Applied_state_assignment.assigned_to">
This attribute indicates the subject which has or is in a <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Applied_state_assignment  Attribute: described_state 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Applied_state_assignment.described_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Applied_state_assignment.described_state">
This attribute indicates a <b>State</b> the subject has or is in.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Composition_of_state  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Composition_of_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Composition_of_state">
Composition of state is a type of state relationship and it relates the nature of states 
in relation to one another, where part(s) of <b>State</b> compose a whole <b>State</b>; and furthermore, 
whole states can become parts of yet another whole <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Composition_of_state  Attribute: part 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Composition_of_state.part"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Composition_of_state.part">
This attribute indicates part(s) of state composition within a whole <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Composition_of_state  Attribute: whole 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Composition_of_state.whole"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Composition_of_state.whole">
This attribute indicates a whole <b>State</b> which contain part(s) of its state composition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Defined_state_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Defined_state_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Defined_state_relationship">
Defined state relationship relates an asserted Verified state to its evaluated State assessment.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Defined_state_relationship  Attribute: defined 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Defined_state_relationship.defined"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Defined_state_relationship.defined">
This attribute indicates the asserted Verified state being related to the evaluated subject <b>State</b> from State 
assessment.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Defined_state_relationship  Attribute: evaluated 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Defined_state_relationship.evaluated"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Defined_state_relationship.evaluated">
This attribute indicates the State assessment being related to the defined and asserted subject <b>State</b> from 
Verified state.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Sequence_of_state  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Sequence_of_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Sequence_of_state">
Sequence of state is a type of state relationship and it relates the sequence of two or more
states in relation to one another.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Sequence_of_state  Attribute: predecessor 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Sequence_of_state.predecessor"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Sequence_of_state.predecessor">
This attribute indicates the predecessor <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Sequence_of_state  Attribute: successor 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Sequence_of_state.successor"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Sequence_of_state.successor">
This attribute indicates the successor <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State">
A <b>State</b> is a state of being.  A state's existence can be just a state, a predicted state, 
or an observed state.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State.name">
A name for the <b>State</b>.
<note> Identifiers can be assigned to the <b>State</b>.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State.description">
A description of the <b>State</b>.  The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_assessment  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_assessment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_assessment">
State assessment uses Condition evaluation to determine whether the subject <b>State</b> 
falls into a particular State definition, which are types of <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_assessment  Attribute: assert_to 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_assessment.assert_to"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_assessment.assert_to">
This attribute indicates a particular State definition the subject <b>State</b> is being evaluated against.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_assessment  Attribute: evaluation 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_assessment.evaluation"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_assessment.evaluation">
This attribute evaluates the subject <b>State</b> with a particular State definition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_assessment  Attribute: subject_state 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_assessment.subject_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_assessment.subject_state">
This attribute indicates the subject <b>State</b> for evaluation against a particular State definition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_cause_effect  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_cause_effect"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_cause_effect">
State cause effect is a type of state relationship and it relates two or more states as 
one state causing particular resulting effect state(s).  In turn, an effect state can 
become a new causing state yielding in yet more effect states.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_cause_effect  Attribute: cause 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_cause_effect.cause"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_cause_effect.cause">
This attribute indicates a <b>State</b> causing an effect <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_cause_effect  Attribute: effect 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_cause_effect.effect"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_cause_effect.effect">
This attribute indicates a <b>State</b> resulting from a cause <b>State</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_observed  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_observed"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_observed">
State observed is an actual <b>State</b> that is observed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_predicted  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_predicted"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_predicted">
State predicted is an actual <b>State</b> that is predicted.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: state_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.state_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship">
State relationship relates two or more states to one another.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_relationship  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_relationship.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship.name">
A name for the State relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_relationship  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_relationship.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship.description">
A description of the State relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: state_relationship_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.state_relationship_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship_relationship">
State relationship relationship relates two or more state relationships to one another.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_relationship_relationship  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_relationship_relationship.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship_relationship.name">
A description of the State relationship relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_relationship_relationship  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_relationship_relationship.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship_relationship.description">
A description of the State relationship relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: state_relationship_relationship  Attribute: related 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.state_relationship_relationship.related"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship_relationship.related">
This attribute identifies the related State relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: state_relationship_relationship  Attribute: relating 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.state_relationship_relationship.relating"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_relationship_relationship.relating">
This attribute identifies the relating State relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_transition  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_transition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_transition">
State transition is a type of state relationship and it relates two or more states before and 
after a transition in <b>State</b>, where at least one <b>State</b> is a start state and at least one <b>State</b> 
is an end state.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_transition  Attribute: end_state 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_transition.end_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_transition.end_state">
This attribute indicates an end state after transition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: State_transition  Attribute: start_state 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.State_transition.start_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.State_transition.start_state">
This attribute indicates a start state before transition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Verified_state  
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Verified_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Verified_state">
Verified state uses Condition evaluation to indicate that the subject <b>State</b> 
falls into a particular State definition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Verified_state  Attribute: asserted_state 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Verified_state.asserted_state"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Verified_state.asserted_state">
This attribute indicates the subject <b>State</b> which is verified to a particular State definition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Verified_state  Attribute: condition_conformance 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Verified_state.condition_conformance"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Verified_state.condition_conformance">
This attribute evaluates the subject <b>State</b> for conformance with a particular State definition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: State_observed_arm  Entity: Verified_state  Attribute: state_conformance 
   <express_ref linkend="state_observed:arm:State_observed_arm.Verified_state.state_conformance"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="State_observed_arm.Verified_state.state_conformance">
This attribute indicates the particular State definition the subject <b>State</b> conforms to.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
